-- Solvay to Spend 83 Million Euros Revamping Tavaux Plant to Cut Emissions
-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 2010-11-09T07:10:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/solvay-to-spend-83-million-euros-revamping-tavaux-plant-to-cut-emissions.html
Solvay SA said it will spend 83
million euros by the end of 2012 to convert the electrolysis
unit of its plant in Tavaux, France, to membrane-based
technology, reducing electricity consumption by 25 percent and
cutting carbon dioxide emissions by 19,200 metric tons annually,
according to an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Martens at 
 jmartens1@bloomberg.net  